Lectura de la base de datos.

DistribuciÃ³n de la especie Hybanthus prunifolius (flor de lluvia) con un DAP mayor de 5 cm.

hp1<-read.csv2("Hp.csv",enc="latin1")

Uso del paquete spatstat

require(spatstat)
## Loading required package: spatstat
## 
## spatstat 1.41-1       (nickname: 'Ides of March') 
## For an introduction to spatstat, type 'beginner'
## 
## Note: spatstat version 1.41-1 is out of date by more than 11 weeks; a newer version should be available.
## Convertir a un objeto de patrones de puntos
pdp1<-ppp(hp1$x,hp1$y,c(0,1000),c(0,500),unitname="metres")

## GrÃ¡fica del objeto de patrones de puntos.
plot(pdp1)

## Resumen del objeto de patrones de puntos.
summary(pdp1)
## Planar point pattern:  450 points
## Average intensity 9e-04 points per square metres
## 
## Coordinates are given to 1 decimal place
## i.e. rounded to the nearest multiple of 0.1 metres
## 
## Window: rectangle = [0, 1000] x [0, 500] metres
## Window area = 5e+05 square metres
## Unit of length: 1 metres

CÃ¡lculo de la densidad mediante cuadrantes.

Prueba de hipÃ³teis para saber si los puntos se distribuyen al azar o tienen algÃºn patrÃ³n.

CC1<-quadratcount(pdp1,nx=10,ny=5)
CC1
##            x
## y           [0,100] (100,200] (200,300] (300,400] (400,500] (500,600]
##   (400,500]      16        16        32        23         4         6
##   (300,400]       8        18        21         3         9         8
##   (200,300]      18        19         7         5         2         7
##   (100,200]      19         9         4         7         9        15
##   [0,100]         4         7         6         7         6         7
##            x
## y           (600,700] (700,800] (800,900] (900,1e+03]
##   (400,500]         6         7         3           2
##   (300,400]         3         8         1           1
##   (200,300]         9         8         4          10
##   (100,200]         5        14         8          12
##   [0,100]          11         6         9           1
plot(pdp1,pch=1)
plot(CC1,add=TRUE,col="red")

quadrat.test(pdp1,nx=10,ny=5)
## 
##  Chi-squared test of CSR using quadrat counts
##  Pearson X2 statistic
## 
## data:  pdp1
## X2 = 223.56, df = 49, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: two.sided
## 
## Quadrats: 10 by 5 grid of tiles
quadrat.test(pdp1,alternative="regular",nx=10,ny=5)
## 
##  Chi-squared test of CSR using quadrat counts
##  Pearson X2 statistic
## 
## data:  pdp1
## X2 = 223.56, df = 49, p-value = 1
## alternative hypothesis: regular
## 
## Quadrats: 10 by 5 grid of tiles
quadrat.test(pdp1,alternative="clustered",nx=10,ny=5)
## 
##  Chi-squared test of CSR using quadrat counts
##  Pearson X2 statistic
## 
## data:  pdp1
## X2 = 223.56, df = 49, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: clustered
## 
## Quadrats: 10 by 5 grid of tiles

GrÃ¡fica de la estimaciÃ³n usando el K de Ripley.

plot(Kest(pdp1))

##        lty col    key                    label
## iso      1   1    iso   italic(hat(K)[iso](r))
## trans    2   2  trans italic(hat(K)[trans](r))
## border   3   3 border  italic(hat(K)[bord](r))
## theo     4   4   theo       italic(K[pois](r))
##                                       meaning
## iso      isotropic-corrected estimate of K(r)
## trans  translation-corrected estimate of K(r)
## border      border-corrected estimate of K(r)
## theo                 theoretical Poisson K(r)

ModelaciÃ³n de patrones de puntos
